Simulate Conway's Game of Life.

Usage: life [OPTIONS]
Example: life -kxs50 -i40

Options:
    -c, --columns       Columns of the board. Default is 30.
    -d, --delay         Delay time between generations in miliseconds. Default is 1.
    -f, --file          Load local CSV file as preset.
    -i, --initial_life  How much life appears in the first generation. Default is 20.
    -k, --kill          If the game enters a loop, exit.
    -l, --load          Load preset as initial configuration.
    -p, --print         Printing mode (0-12). Default is 0.
    -r, --rows          Rows of the board. Default is 30.
    -s, --size          Size of the board in rows and columns.
    -t, --termsize      Adjust the size to the terminal dimensions.
    -x, --data          Display the amount of life and number of the generation.
    -h, --help          Show this message!
  
Print modes:
    0   Tiny
    1   Squares
    2   Half-width squares
    3   Reversed squares
    4   Chess
    5   Binary
    6   Non-binary
    7   ASCII (#)
    8   ASCII (@)
    9   ASCII (*)
    10  Gay
    11  meow :3
    12  ðŸ¥º

Default presets:
    glider    pentonimo   diehard acorn   snake   infinity1   infinity2
    gun       cloverleaf  ants    loss    amogus

INSTALL:
    curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ivaaane/life/refs/heads/main/install.sh | bash